Wing (
Fig. 3
) clear, but anterior two cells brownish tinged. Veins black and weakly seamed brown.

Legs (
Fig 3
). Fore leg. Tarsomere 4 with an apical fork, the inner prong (anterior) much longer than the outer (posterior) prong. Tarsomere 5 with an apical protuberance. Ratio of femur, tibia and tarsomeres in mm: 1.4: 1.2: 0.9: 0.2: 0.3: 0.16: 0.2.
